This map is just like xmas_icecastle except the music has been removed. If you want to play with the christmas music, please download the original xmas_icecastle. It can be downloaded here: http://www.fpsbanana.com/maps/118876

Here is a fun little Christmas map for your holiday amusement. The Ice Castle is home to crystals that produce Christmas spirit. The terrorists are bent on destroying the crystals and ruining Christmas for everyone.

Here are a few hints and tips for navigating your way around the map:
- The dual speed track is just like the Slideracer maps. The snowmen, bombs and Santa Furby will instakill you, so be careful!
- To control the track speed, shoot the corresponding targets over the track.
- The Castle contains speed tubes that let you quickly go up, down or side to side. Follow the arrows for the proper direction.
- There are also arrow ramps on the roof that let you long jump from one roof to the other. Make sure you jump at the very edge or you will miss the other side. Cross jump at your own peril.
- There are 3 bomb sites. Site A is at the Christmas tree immediately below CT spawn. Site B is on the roof at CT spawn. Site C is located on the balcony overlooking the massive power cube in the Castle opposite CT spawn.

This is the same map as xmas_icecastle minus the music.  If you like the music then download the other one!

Strategy:
Terrorists
- If you have the bomb, try not to die on the track. It is really difficult for your teammates to locate and pick up the bomb when moving at high speed.
- With three bomb sites to choose from, try to get a jump on the CTs by finding the site they’re not defending.

Counter Terrorists
- Cover all bomb sites and get to them quickly. CTs have the advantage of getting to any bomb site faster than the Ts. It is essential to have your teammates get in position quickly to defend each bomb site and signal where the bomb is going.
- Determine where the sites are located and the fastest way to get to them. Knowing the fastest way from site to site is really important!

Secret Area:
There is a secret area in the map. It is not easy to find but I’ll leave you a Jumble. http://www.natcarm.com/castle_jumble.jpg (stirred and course are NOT correct answers)

This map is currently playing at the following server address:

This is a year old map of mine, a port of the even older map xmas_apehouse from 1.6 to source. Figured I should put it on fpsbanana.


from the .txt:

***********************************
xmas_apehouse_s

Made by HomicidalApe.

email: dantoumey@gmail.com

http://www.homicidalape.mybigspoon.com/mapsite
***********************************

	A family living in a house in the winter on december 25th suddenly up and left with all the doors unlocked. A bunch of terrorists decided to go in the house and plant a bomb next to a tree that is in their living room for some reason. Counter-Terrorists are only coming to the house because they heard it was empty and they wanted to party in it. Forces collide.

Terrorsits: Plant the bomb under the tree that is decorated for some reason and in the living room.

Counter-Terrorist: Try to party it up without getting killed by terrorists. Killing the terrorists is ok, but if they all die the round starts over and you can't party in the house. Plus if they plant the bomb then your party time will run out, try to not let them plant it. Use arguement and reason, not force.

HINT: There's a ladder to the roof of the house somewhere!

A defuse map with a twist. The T's start in the bombsite, a warehouse with secret intel. Their plan is to blow it up to prevent the CT's gathering their special intel. While the T's are planting the bomb the CT's have to get their in time, equipped with a defuser already. There are many places to enter the warehouse. Some include the front and side door. A climbing place. A tree house connection. Make a tactic with your team and stop the T's from blowing up the intel. Recommended to play with a longer bomb. (Preferably around 40 seconds - 90 seconds) Still in beta. Tell me what should I improve on.

This map includes 3 vehicules for now, and 4 more are to be add later, one is really fast (the Bike), another is less speedy but has two places, one being a gunner position, and the last one (can be taken by choosing to pass through the vehicule door at the spawn), is a Giant Bipod, equipped with a laser and a rocket launcher being also able to jump.

At the Spawn you can choose through multiple super powers (Extra Life, Heal, Super Speed, Invisibility), there are two levels of each, but you can't choose the same twice, depending on whether you choose one, two (or none) you'll get more or less "good" weapons.

Finally, don't be scared, this is a dynamic map, the layer will change randomly adding to the uniqueness of this map.

UPEx for CS:S
===================
2011 UPDATE FOR CURRENT SOURCE ENGINE
===================
[http://ihmaps.com/](http://ihmaps.com/ "Innocent Hawk Maps")

Description
===================
In harsh economic times international package shipping giants UPS and FedEx were at risk of going bankrupt. The government refused to give them bailout money, as the banks and automotive companies had already taken the money. To save themselves, a merger took place between UPS and FedEx to form: UPEx. With all of their resources and business combined they could once again thrive, however some of the stock holders of both companies disagreed with the merger. With rage in their hearts and the Anarchist's Cookbook in their hands, they joined together to terrorize the newly formed UPEx. Will the Counter-Terrorists be able to stop them? Or will UPEx crumble at the hands of an angry Wall Street?

Full map name: de_UPEx_2011
Map type: DE (Bomb/Defuse)
.BSP file size: 21,829 KB
Release date: Friday, April 8, 2011

Bombsites: Office (A) and Hazardous Materials Cage (B)
Map Theme: An international package shipping hub.
Special Features: The Hazardous Materials Cage (B) is a double-decker bomb point, meaning the bomb can be planted above or below ground.

Players: 16-32 recommended, 40 maximum
Custom Textures: Yes
Custom Sounds: No
Custom Models: No
.NAV File: Yes, but it is just the auto-generated navigation mesh.

Map tips: Throw grenades over the cubicle walls and climb on room objects to peek over the walls when guarding A.
Remember that B is a double-decker bomb point. Below has more cover for planting, but less places to hide while guarding. Above has less cover for planting, but more places to hide while guarding.

Installation
===================

Extract the .BSP and .Nav files to "...\Steam\steamapps\username\counter-strike source\cstrike\maps"

Simple, right? :)

Special Thanks
===================

Also thanks to all the hard work that has gone into creating tutorials at:
